Class DJIPhantomMainController

  • java.lang.Object
    • dji.sdk.api.DJIObject
      • dji.sdk.api.MainController.DJIMainController
        • dji.sdk.api.MainController.DJIPhantomMainController

  • public class DJIPhantomMainController
extends DJIMainController

    DJI Phantom Main Controller Class

    Extending the DJIMainController, DJIPhantomMainController is designed for Phantom. DJIMainController provides a series of information and status about the drone. Customers could monitor the instant message by using this class. Every 1000ms, the callback of MainController would send back the message the drone contains.

    Also, the mainController requires that developers correctly construct the life cycle. There is a tutorial for setting up the life cycle.

    private DJIMcuUpdateStateCallBack mMcuUpdateStateCallBack = null;
